com.mnnit.tutorspoint.core

Class User

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mnnit.tutorspoint.core.User

  • public class User
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a user.
    A user is simply a container for a username and password.
    The recommended way of building user objects is using the UserBuilder class.

    A user can be constructed using UserBuilder or using the User(String, String, UserType) constructor.

    For example,


    User user = new User("foo", "bar"); user.setPassword("dasd"); // or whatever

    See Also:
    UserBuilder
